                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "We can already have an \"all of the above\" world – for a long time we could have an IDE that puts a code view next to an assembly view next to a hexdump – Microsoft Visual IDEs could pivot between graphical and code views – plenty of productivity tools like Notion and Zenkit are now comfortable with \"view pivots\" (between table view, list view, kanban view, mind map, calendar, whatever)\n\nPivotability is what's core, then we can all have what we like"
